full_text: Screened by NARA, 6/7/2023 TED STATES OF AMERICA DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE IMMIGRATION AND NATURALIZATION SERVICE WARRANT OF DEPORTATION No. A28-417-099 To any Officer or Employee of the United States Immigration and Naturalization Service. After due hearing before an authorized officer of the United States Immigration and Naturalization Service, and upon the basis thereof, an order has been duly made that the alien FONSECA, Terencio who entered the United States at UNKNOWN on or about the 23rd day of 4 April 87 , 19 , is subject to deportation under the following provisions of the laws of the United States, to wit: Section 241 (a)(2) of the Immigration and Nationality Act, I, the undersigned officer of the United States, by virtue of the power and authority vested in the Attorney General under the laws of the United States and by his direction, command you to take into custody and deport the said alien pursuant to law, at the expense of the appropriation Salaries & Expenses. Immigration and Naturalization Service. 1992 including the expenses of an attendant. If necessary. Signature: Richard B Smith Title: District Director Date: December 1, 1990 Place: Miami, Florida orm I-205 Rev.11-29-79)N
